summary: Main text is an s. xiin copy of the Latin version of Bede’s Historia ecclesiastica, written in English Caroline minuscule. Cædmon’s Hymn is added on the bottom margin of fol. 129. Place of production not known.

notes.head: Incipit
notes.body: (fol. 129) Nu we sculon herian heofonrices weard

notes.head: Explicit
notes.body: (fol. 129) Æfter tida firum on foldum frea ælmyhtig

admin: Manuscript described by Mary Swan and Owen Roberson with the assistance of Hollie Morgan, with reference to published scholarship (2012).
